Sixty-Six Wards Live 2018 Primary Election Tracker

Welcome to the Sixty-Six Wards turnout tracker! Voters across Philadelphia are sharing their turnout to support citizen science.

First, vote! Then, share your Division and Voter Number at http://bit.ly/sixtysixturnout.

Live Results

As of 07:12, 566 voters in 51 wards have shared their voter number. I estimate that 187,435 people have voted across the city (95% Confidence Interval: 172,444 - 202,967).

[Note: the 165,382 represents 2014 Democratic Primary votes cast for Governor. For annoying reasons, I’m using that rather than actual 2014 Dem turnout. That’s lower than the 173,229 who actually showed up at the polls. Thanks to Commissioner Schmidt for reminding me to point this out.]

Maps

I use historical correlations among divisions’ turnout to estimate turnout in the divisions with no data yet. I simultaneously estimate (1) the overall city-wide turnout, (2) divisions’ over-/under-performance, and (3) the city-wide time pattern of voting.

Here are the current estimates of turnout in each division.
